body:
### Props be first
The whole thing is inspired by David Fowler's [example code](https://github.com/davidfowl/SignalR.Relay).

### What is SignalGrr?
SignalGrr is just an angrier, more impulsive [SignalR](https://github.com/SignalR/SignalR) proxy server. Why angrier? I'm not sure. Why more impulsive? Because it's so damn simple to spin up a hub using pure javascript. I made two simple jquery plugins using SignalGrr already: [jquery.signalRamp.js - easy UI syncing](http://timheckel.github.com/SignalRamp/)  and [jquery.zyngaScroller.js - real-time kinetic scrolling](http://timheckel.github.com/ZyngaScroller/). 

### Can you handle it?
It's so convenient, it made me want to shove it up on [AppHarbor](http://appharbor.com), so that's precisely what I did after upgrading the code to use the latest SignalR 1.0.0 javascript client and pulling the latest code from the SignalR repository.

On AppHarbor, SignalGrr is available either

http://signalGrr.apphb.com
OR
https://signalGrr.apphb.com

Now, if you're just wanting to schlep data between clients, stop worrying about the server side hub. Just write `var conn = $.hubConnection("http://signalGrr.apphb.com")` inside your javascript and you've got your entire hub!

### DISCLAIMER
I know SignalR Alpha is nearing completion, so the api will likely change. I'll do my best to keep SignalGrr up to date with the latest javascript client and code.

### Client Usage
This is inspired by David's original source:

```
$(function () {
  var connection = $.hubConnection("http://signalgrr.apphb.com"),
    chat = connection.createProxy('chat');

    chat.on('foo', function (n) {
        console.log(n);
    });

    connection.start().done(function () {
        chat.invoke('foo', "If Jimmy Chitwood transfers to Terhune, we don't have a prayer this year.");
    });
});
```

### Big Picture
SignalR as an application framework has resonated with me for a long time, especially in a world with [these crazy ideas bursting forth](http://meteor.com). I have some ideas regarding data persistence inside the [jquery.signalRamp.js](http://timheckel.github.com/SignalRamp) concept, but alas that's a larger topic. More to come.
